{Machinery }
There are many machines on the farm which make work much easier, such as bulldozers, tractors, a plough, a double chopper, a flail and chopper, a caterpillar bulldozer, a picker bail, a combine harvester, a cultivator, crop sprayer and a book raker.
{Milking}
The milking parlour is 12 years old. It contains 10 units which include 10 feeders and 10 dust removers. They are disinfected regularly with hyper- chloride. The cows are milked twice a day, in the morning at 6.30 a.m. and later in the day at about 5.00 p.m.
